On{Saturday 1st. June 1985}the people of Old Kilpatrick celebrated their annual{Gala Day.}
I woke up that morning to find the sun shining brightly in my bedroom window. It was such a lovely day, just perfect for the{Gala.}I was so excited. The{Gala}began with a parade of floats.
The one I liked best carried {Charlene Robertson}who was chosen to be this years{Gala Queen.}She was sitting on her throne with a lovely blue dress and a diamond crown. Her attendants were standing at either side of her. On the night of the{Gala Queen's {Coronation}the children of the village took part in a{concert. .}Contd.page 3 .
